1. Information we may collect

Idle Traffic Tycoon collects information in order to provide better services to all users. The main sources of information collected by Survivors Puzzles are: information you provide to Survivors Puzzles, information obtained by Survivors Puzzles during your use of Survivors Puzzles products and services, and your information shared by third parties. The types of information collected by Survivors Puzzles mainly include the following:

1. Personal information

Personal information refers to various information that can be individually or combined with other information to identify the personal identity of a natural person, including but not limited to the natural person’s name, date of birth, ID number, personal biometric information, address, Phone number etc.

When you register an account or use Survivors Puzzles products and services, with your consent and confirmation, Survivors Puzzles may collect the relevant personal information you provide, such as name, gender, age, date of birth, ID number, bank card number , Email address, phone number, mailing address, occupation, education level, etc.

2. Equipment information

Equipment information refers to the information of the equipment used when you use Survivors Puzzles products or services.

When you use Survivors Puzzles products or services, Survivors Puzzles will collect information about the devices you use Survivors Puzzles products or services, such as device name, device model, device identification code, operating system and application version, language settings, Resolution, service provider network ID (pLMN), etc. This information can help Survivors Puzzles provide you with better information display or product services.

3. Location information

Location information refers to the information about your location collected when you turn on the device positioning function and use the related services provided by Survivors Puzzles based on location, including:

(1) When you turn on the device positioning function and use Survivors Puzzles related products or services, Survivors Puzzles may use GpS, WiFi or other technical methods to collect and process information about your actual location.

(2) Real-time information including your geographic location provided by you or other users. For example, shared information uploaded by you or others showing your current or previous geographic location, and geotag information contained in photos shared by you or others.

(3) If you do not want to be accessed, you can choose to turn off the relevant functions of the device or product/service, but this may affect Survivors Puzzles to provide you with relevant services.

4. Log information

Refers to when you use Survivors Puzzles products and services, the system may automatically collect certain information through cookies or other methods and store it in server logs. Such information may include:

(1) Detailed usage of Survivors Puzzles products and services, such as the web search terms you use, the page address you visit, and other information and content details that you browse or request when using Survivors Puzzles services; user habits Statistical data, such as setting item information when using the Survivors Puzzles input method, the number of uses of some buttons, the number of words on the screen, etc. This type of data is anonymous, and Survivors Puzzles cannot locate specific users based on the uploaded data .

(2) Device or software information, such as the configuration information provided by your mobile device, web browser or other programs used to access Survivors Puzzles products or services, the version and device identification code used by the mobile device, etc.

(3) Equipment event information, such as crashes, system activities, etc.

(4) Ip address.

5. Other information collected after your consent.


