(1) We may use the collected information for the following purposes:

1. When Survivors Puzzles provides products and services, it is used for identity verification, customer service, security protection, archiving and backup, etc., to ensure the safety of the products and services provided by Survivors Puzzles to you.

2. Guarantee the normal realization of the product or service function provided for you. For example: In order to realize your personalized recommendation function, understand how you access and use Survivors Puzzles's products and services, so as to respond to your personalized needs, such as language settings, location settings, and personalized Help services and instructions, or make other responses to you and other users, etc.

3. Improve the existing products and services of Survivors Puzzles and enhance the user experience. E.g

(1) Survivors Puzzles may collect your browsing information, your interests and hobbies (you can choose in the account settings) for data analysis, to show you the service information you are interested in; or to show you when you search Show the content of the information you might want to find.

(2) Survivors Puzzles may also obtain other information about you for reasonable needs to provide services and improve service quality, including relevant information you provide when you contact customer service, and the questionnaire sent to Survivors Puzzles when you participate in the questionnaire survey Reply information and related information obtained by Survivors Puzzles when you interact with Survivors Puzzles.

(3) For the information collected from your various devices, Survivors Puzzles may associate them so that they can provide you with consistent services on these devices.

(4) Survivors Puzzles may combine information from a certain service with information from other services in order to provide you with services, personalized content and suggestions.

4. Help Survivors Puzzles design new products and services. For example, when Survivors Puzzles provides certain products or services, it may invite users to participate in the "User Experience Improvement Program". For users who join the user experience improvement program, Survivors Puzzles will perform the use of various functions of the products and services as needed. Statistics, in this way, the quality of products and services can be improved by analyzing statistical data, and innovative products and services that are helpful to users can be launched. If you don't want to participate in the program, you can choose to turn off the related functions in the related products/services.

5. Survivors Puzzles may use your relevant information to provide you with more relevant advertising or promotional information. Survivors Puzzles may also use your information to send you marketing information through Survivors Puzzles's services, e-mail or other means, to provide or promote Survivors Puzzles or third-party goods and services. If you do not want Survivors Puzzles to use your personal information for the aforementioned purposes, you can request Survivors Puzzles to stop using your personal information for the aforementioned purposes through the relevant channels provided in Survivors Puzzles related products or services.

6. Software certification or management software upgrade.

7. According to laws and regulations, collect and use your relevant information in the following situations, in which case your authorization is not required:

(1) Related to national security and national defense security;

(2) Related to public safety, public health, and major public interests;

(3) Related to criminal investigation, prosecution, trial, and execution of judgments;

(4) It is difficult to obtain the consent of the individual in order to protect the life, property and other major legal rights of the personal information subject or other individuals;

(5) Necessary for maintaining the safe and stable operation of the products and/or services provided, such as discovering and disposing of product and/or service failures;

(6) Necessary for legal news reports;

(7) When it is necessary for academic research institutions to conduct statistical or academic research based on the public interest, and when they provide academic research or description results to the outside, they de-identify the personal information contained in the results;

(8) Other circumstances stipulated by laws and regulations.

8. Other purposes approved by you.

In order to provide you with a better experience, improve Survivors Puzzles’s products and services, or for other purposes you agree to, and subject to relevant laws and regulations, Survivors Puzzles may use information collected through a certain product or service, Used in other products and services of Survivors Puzzles in an aggregated or personalized way. For example, the information collected when you use one of Survivors Puzzles's services may be used in another service to provide you with specific content, or to show you related, non-general push information. If Survivors Puzzles provides corresponding options in related services, you can also authorize Survivors Puzzles to use the information provided and stored by the service for other services of Survivors Puzzles.

(2) Rules for the use of your personal information

1. Survivors Puzzles will use the collected information in accordance with the provisions of this privacy policy and to realize Survivors Puzzles's product and/or service functions.

2. After collecting your personal information, Survivors Puzzles will de-identify the data through technical means, and the de-identified information will not be able to identify the subject. Please understand and agree that in this case, Survivors Puzzles has the right to use de-identified information; and without disclosing your personal information, it has the right to analyze the user database and make commercial use.

3. Please note that all personal information you provide when you use Survivors Puzzles’s products and/or services, unless you delete or refuse collection by Survivors Puzzles through system settings, it will be used when you use Survivors Puzzles’s products and/or services. / Or continue to authorize Survivors Puzzles to use during the service period. When you log out of your account, Survivors Puzzles will stop using and delete your personal information.

4. Survivors Puzzles will make statistics on the use of Survivors Puzzles's products and/or services, and may share these statistical information with the public or third parties to show the overall usage trend of Survivors Puzzles's products and/or services. But these statistics do not contain any identifying information about you.

5. When Survivors Puzzles displays your personal information, Survivors Puzzles will desensitize your information including content replacement and anonymization to protect your information security.

6. When Survivors Puzzles wants to use your personal information for other purposes not specified in this policy, or when the information collected for a specific purpose is used for other purposes, it will use you to actively check in advance. Seek your consent.


3. Information sharing, transfer and disclosure

(1) Sharing of information

1. Survivors Puzzles will not share your personal information with any company, organization or individual other than Survivors Puzzles, except in the following circumstances:

(1) Obtain your explicit consent or authorization in advance;

(2) Provide in accordance with applicable laws and regulations, legal procedures, mandatory administrative or judicial requirements;

(3) To the extent permitted by laws and regulations, it is necessary to provide Survivors Puzzles or its partners, you or other users Survivors Puzzles,or the public from damages to their interests, property or safety;

(4) Only by sharing your information can the core functions of Survivors Puzzles's products and/or services be realized or the services you need can be provided;

(5) Dealing with disputes or disputes between you and others according to your needs;

(6) Provided in accordance with the relevant agreement signed with you (including the electronic agreement signed online and the corresponding platform rules) or other legal documents;

(7) Use based on academic research;

(8) Use based on social public interest in compliance with laws and regulations.

2.Survivors Puzzles may share your personal information with affiliates of Survivors Puzzles。 However, Survivors Puzzles will only share necessary personal information and is subject to this privacy policy. If the affiliates of Survivors Puzzles want to change the purpose of processing personal information, they will again seek your authorization and consent.

3. Survivors Puzzles may share your information with partners and other third parties to ensure the smooth completion of the services provided to you. However, Survivors Puzzles will only share your personal information for legal, legitimate, necessary, specific and clear purposes, and will only share personal information necessary to provide services. The partners of Survivors Puzzles have no right to use the shared personal information for any other purpose.

4. For companies, organizations and individuals with whom Survivors Puzzles shares personal information, Survivors Puzzles will require them to abide by their confidentiality agreement, requiring them to follow the instructions of Survivors Puzzles, this privacy policy and any other related confidentiality and security measures To process personal information.

5. In order to comply with the law, to implement or apply Survivors Puzzles's conditions of use and other agreements, or to protect the rights of Survivors Puzzles, you or other Survivors Puzzles customers and their property or safety, such as to prevent fraud and other illegal activities and reduce Credit risk while exchanging information with other companies and organizations. However, this does not include personal information that is sold, rented, shared or otherwise disclosed for profit in violation of the commitments made in this privacy policy.

(2) Transfer of information

Survivors Puzzles will not transfer your personal information to any company, organization or individual, except in the following cases:

(1) Obtain your explicit consent or authorization in advance;

(2) Provide in accordance with applicable laws and regulations, legal procedures, mandatory administrative or judicial requirements;

(3) Provided in accordance with relevant agreements signed with you (including electronic agreements signed online and corresponding platform rules) or other legal documents;

(4) When it comes to mergers, acquisitions, asset transfers or similar transactions, if it involves the transfer of personal information, Survivors Puzzles will require new companies and organizations that hold your personal information to continue to be bound by this privacy policy, otherwise, Survivors Puzzles will ask the company or organization to ask you for authorization again.

(3) Disclosure of information

Survivors Puzzles will only publicly disclose your personal information under the following circumstances and adopting industry-standard safety protection measures:

(1) You agree to or authorize Survivors Puzzles to disclose;

(2) You use the sharing function;

(3) In cases where your personal information must be provided in accordance with the requirements of laws, regulations, mandatory administrative law enforcement or judicial requirements, Survivors Puzzles may publicly disclose your personal information based on the required personal information types and disclosure methods. Under the premise of complying with laws and regulations, when Survivors Puzzles receives the above request for disclosure of information, Survivors Puzzles will require the corresponding legal documents to be issued. Survivors Puzzles has carefully reviewed all requests to ensure It has a legal basis and is limited to data obtained by law enforcement agencies for specific investigation purposes and with legal rights;

(4) In an emergency, to protect the legal rights or public safety and interests of you, Survivors Puzzles and other users;

(5) Comply with the user agreement of Survivors Puzzles related products and services or other similar agreements.


Fourth, our information security protection

1. Idle Traffic Tycoon will only retain your personal information for the period necessary for the purpose described in this policy and within the time limit required by laws and regulations.

2. Data security technical measures: Survivors Puzzles will adopt security protection measures that meet industry standards, including establishing reasonable system specifications and security technologies to prevent your personal information from unauthorized access, use, modification, and data damage Or lost; Survivors Puzzles will use security technology and procedures to monitor and record network operation status and network security incidents, and take necessary technical measures to ensure network security to prevent information loss, improper use, unauthorized reading or disclosure. For example, in some services, Survivors Puzzles will use encryption technology to protect the personal information you provide. However, please understand that due to technical limitations and various malicious methods that may exist, in the Internet industry, even if you do your best to strengthen security measures, it is impossible to always guarantee 100% security of information. You need to understand that the system and communication network you use to access Survivors Puzzles's products and services may have problems due to factors outside the controllable range of Survivors Puzzles.

3. Survivors Puzzles only allows employees and partners who need to know this information to access personal information, and has set up strict access control and monitoring mechanisms for this purpose. Survivors Puzzles also requires all persons who may have access to your personal information to perform corresponding confidentiality obligations. If you fail to fulfill these obligations, you may be held accountable or be suspended from the partnership with Survivors Puzzles.

4. Survivors Puzzles will take all reasonable and feasible measures to ensure that irrelevant personal information is not collected. Survivors Puzzles will only retain your personal information for the period required to achieve the purpose stated in the policy, unless it is necessary to extend the retention period or is permitted by law.

5. The content and information you provide, upload or publish when you use Survivors Puzzles's products and services (such as photos and other information about your personal activities) may reveal your personal information. You need to carefully consider whether to disclose relevant personal information when using Survivors Puzzles's products and services. In some cases, you can control the range of users who have the right to browse your shared information through the privacy settings of certain products and services of Survivors Puzzles.

6. The Internet is not an absolutely secure environment, and the communication methods with other users such as e-mail, instant messaging, social software, etc. cannot be determined whether it is completely encrypted. Survivors Puzzles recommends that you use complex passwords when using such tools, and take care to protect you Security of personal information.

7. Security incident handling: In order to deal with possible risks such as personal information leakage, damage and loss, Survivors Puzzles has established a special emergency response team, in accordance with the company’s relevant security incident handling specifications, and launches security plans for different security incidents. Stop loss, analyze, formulate remedial measures, and cooperate with relevant departments to trace the source and crack down. At the same time, Survivors Puzzles will promptly inform you in accordance with the requirements of laws and regulations: the basic situation and possible impact of the security incident, the disposal measures that Survivors Puzzles has taken or will take, and suggestions that you can prevent and reduce risks on your own. Remedial measures, etc. At the same time, Survivors Puzzles will promptly notify you of the incident by e-mail, letter, telephone, push notification, etc. If it is difficult to inform the subject of personal information one by one, Survivors Puzzles will take a reasonable and effective way to issue an announcement. At the same time, Survivors Puzzles will also proactively report the handling of personal information security incidents in accordance with the requirements of the regulatory authorities.


5. Your management of personal information

1. You have the right to access, correct, and delete your personal information; however, the deletion or modification of related information may affect your use of related products or services or lead to the realization of some functions.

2. You have the right to change the scope of your authorization or to withdraw your authorization; you can change the scope or scope of your authorization to continue collecting personal information by Survivors Puzzles by deleting information, turning off device functions, and setting privacy settings in the website or software. Withdraw your authorization. You can also withdraw all authorization of Survivors Puzzles to continue collecting your personal information by canceling your account. Please understand that each business function requires some basic personal information to be completed. After you withdraw your consent or authorization, Survivors Puzzles cannot continue to provide you with services corresponding to the withdrawal of your consent or authorization, and will no longer process your corresponding personal information. However, your decision to withdraw your consent or authorization will not affect the previous processing of personal information based on your authorization.

3. You can also directly apply for cancellation of the relevant product account if the agreed conditions of the relevant product are met. After you cancel your account, Survivors Puzzles will stop providing you with products and/or services, and at your request, unless otherwise provided by laws and regulations, Survivors Puzzles will delete your personal information.

4. Survivors Puzzles will take appropriate technical measures to ensure that you can inquire, supplement, correct or delete your personal information, or apply for Survivors Puzzles’s complaints through the feedback or complaint channels released by Survivors Puzzles related products or services. Information is supplemented, corrected or deleted; after Survivors Puzzles receives your application, it will be processed according to the process (for example, Survivors Puzzles may require you to provide relevant certificates to confirm your identity).

5. If you are unable to access, correct or delete your personal information, or you need to access, correct or delete other personal information generated when you use Survivors Puzzles products and/or services, or if you think Survivors Puzzles has any In violation of laws and regulations or the agreement with you on the collection or use of personal information, you can contact Survivors Puzzles through the official feedback channel of related products or services announced by Survivors Puzzles or through the email bill7605486@gmail.com.


6. Protection of minors' information

1. Survivors Puzzles attaches great importance to the protection of personal information of minors. If you are a minor under the age of 18, you should obtain the consent of your parents or their legal guardian (hereinafter collectively referred to as the "guardian") before submitting your personal information.

2. Survivors Puzzles encourages guardians to guide minors to use Survivors Puzzles's products and services, and recommends that minors encourage their guardians to read this policy.

3. The guardian shall bear the primary responsibility for protecting the privacy of minors in the network environment.

4. Survivors Puzzles will protect the relevant information of minors in accordance with relevant national laws and regulations.


