In addition to the exemptions listed in this policy, Survivors Puzzles does not have to bear any responsibility for the following situations:

1. Any personal information leaked, lost, stolen or tampered with is caused by you telling others the user password, sharing the registered account with others, or because of your personal improper keeping.

2. Any personal information leakage, loss, theft or tampering caused by force majeure that affects the normal operation of the network due to hacking, computer virus intrusion or attack, temporary shutdown due to government control, etc.

3. The leakage of personal information caused by other websites linked to Survivors Puzzles and any legal disputes and consequences arising therefrom.

4. The leakage of personal information caused by other reasons other than Survivors Puzzles and any legal disputes and consequences arising therefrom.


8. The scope of application of this policy

1. This policy applies to all products and services of Survivors Puzzles. Specific privacy policies for certain specific products and services will be specifically specified in the relevant product and service use agreement or a separate privacy agreement. The privacy terms of these specific products and services form part of this policy. If the privacy clauses of related specific products and services are inconsistent with this policy, the privacy clauses of the specific products and services shall apply.

2. This policy only applies to the information collected by Survivors Puzzles, and does not apply to any third-party products and services or third-party information usage rules, such as third-party products accepted through Survivors Puzzles's products and services This policy does not apply to the information collected by the service (including any third-party websites). Survivors Puzzles is not responsible for any third party's use of the information provided by you.

